To evaluate this determinant, we expand it along the first row:

\begin{align*}
\begin{vmatrix}
x & \sin \theta & \cos \theta \\
-\sin \theta & -x & 1 \\
\cos \theta & 1 & x
\end{vmatrix}
&=
x\begin{vmatrix}
-x & 1 \\
1 & x
\end{vmatrix}
-\sin\theta\begin{vmatrix}
-\sin \theta & 1\\
\cos \theta & x
\end{vmatrix}
+\cos \theta \begin{vmatrix}
-\sin \theta & -x\\
\cos \theta & 1
\end{vmatrix}\\
&=x(-x^2-1)-\sin \theta(-\sin \theta x - \cos \theta)+\cos \theta(-\sin \theta -x \cos \theta)\\
&=-x^3-x+\sin^2 \theta x + \sin \theta \cos \theta -\sin \theta \cos \theta-x\cos^2 \theta\\
&=-x^3-x+x(\sin^2 \theta + \cos^2 \theta)\\
&=-x^3-x+x(1)\\
&=-x^3.
\end{align*}

The answer to this question is \boxed{-x^3}.

